               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18460615-name-112" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18460615-name-112" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460615-name-112" type="surname" value="BRANDON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18460615-name-112" type="given" value="ABRAHAM"></interp>ABRAHAM BRANDON</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a boot and shoemaker, and live in Hounds<lb></lb>ditch; the prisoner was in my service. On the 30th of June I gave him a hamper with twenty-four pairs of shoes, thirty-two pairs of women's boots, and, twelve pairs of children's boots—I told him to deliver the greater portion of them to Mr. Joseph Johnson, in Tottenham-court-road, and the remainder to Mr. Pritchard—he never came back to me.</p>
